<TITLE> Explain removal of BSMMU VC: HC to govt </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, November 23 (bdnews24.com) The High Court Sunday issued a rule nisi upon government to show cause as to why removal of Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University vice chancellor MA Tahir should not be declared illegal. A HC division bench of justices Syed Mahmud Hossain and Quamrul Islam Siddique asked the government to reply within two weeks, upon a writ petition filed by professor MA Tahir. The government removed Tahir on Nov 5 following allegations of irregularities, including a forged medical certificate of former BNP lawmaker Mosaddak Ali Falu. Barrister Rafique-ul-Haque moved the petition for Prof Tahir, while deputy attorney general Razique-al-Jalil opposed it. b
